Nehawu says workers will go back to work on Friday despite some outstanding issues before the National Bargaining Council. JOHANNESBURG - The National Health Education &amp; Allied Workers Union (Nehawu) has confirmed that a strike by its members at the Social Development Department has ended.Social workers stopped work for five weeks over wage dissatisfaction and poor working conditions.Nehawu says workers will go back to work on Friday despite some outstanding issues before the National Bargaining Council. So the only thing that we still need to agree on is the issue of the rural allowance and the reviewal of occupation specific dispensation. Once those are finalised then the strike will be called off permanently. 